>Is there a semi-official doc of tags
Well I have a tag-bin: https://pastebin.com/83H7TWuf . This is updated every time I tag a story for I could have a new species or tag. My plan in the future is to separate b/w descriptive and search tags if that makes sense.

>format that your script expects or is easier to sort from?
I don't quite understand specifically what you are asking here so ill try to answer as broadly as possible:

The main format I use for my scripts is a modified version of Deimos_lynx format which looks like the following:

By {Author}

>{title}
{url}

Modified version that I use for my version of the catalog:

By {Author}

[tag1, tag2,][tag3, tag4, tag,5]{symbols}
{url}
#{Description}

Both are compatible with my scripts. Now do note that the scripts are a (WIP) so they are not exactly set in stone at the moment. And may I ask why you would want to know of the format and for what use? Just curious for I only use the scripts for the master bin and my catalogue.

-Azuhmier (aka taganon)
